description.3: The "Molten Man-Thing" has mysteriously risen from a volcanic eruption! He doesn't seem too friendly either!
description.4: A mad artist creates objects that come to life!
description.8: The "Thing from the Swamp" has been uncovered by a group of men! If this monster's intentions aren't pure, they're simply doomed!
description.9: Powerful, angry Stone Men attack Manhattan!
description.13: In order to gain intel on the U.S. Military, a Martian is sent to Earth in a robot's body. But what happens if he's stuck speaking binary forever?
description.14: A pilot crash-lands on an island where everything is completely backwards...
description.19: An alien agent is deployed to Earth to destroy a rocket ship that would give humans the ability to travel to his planet.
description.20: What happens when a film director is kidnapped but his movie's magic might actually be to blame?
description.25: How will humans fare against a superior alien race who now seeks to conquer earth?
description.26: If you're going to travel to the past to gain personal riches, be sure not to lose your time machine...
description.31: A bored human sets his sights on taking over a new world -- Planet X!
description.32: A lucky man soon realizes he is quite unlucky after discovering an alien upon a flying saucer!
description.37: In 2478 mankind is finally able to travel at unthinkable speeds through space. They are going to need all the speed they can get as humans desperately search for a new planet to live on, fleeing from a massively overpopulated Earth!
description.38: Captain Kane and Professor Briggs come across a mysterious place with dangerously oversized creatures.
description.63: If a door could talk...it might tell you to run far away from this place!
description.67: A man is tired of painting, so he gets a robot to do it for him. But just you wait until the machine gets tired of painting too…
description.70: A witch doctor has a mysterious Jack-in-the-Box waiting to be opened…would you take the bait?
description.74: A man thinks he commits a crime and is able to put himself to sleep for forty years in order to not be caught.
description.76: We are in the year 2856. A man tells a story of a haunted antique he once bought…hundreds of years ago!
description.80: Are you scared of the dark? If not, you will be after reading this issue!
description.83: Some of humankind’s greatest fears exist from things much smaller than us. Spiders, wasps…What would happen in a world where they are bigger than us?
description.88: What was waiting at the End of the Line?
description.91: In a yarn spun in the Wild West, a man seems to be a bit different from everyone else…in fact; he seems “Not Quite Human”!

88.text: What was waiting at the End of the Line?

93.text: A group of robbers place themselves and their pile of cash into suspended animation for TWO whole years!

94.text: A Pharaoh and a man from 1956 have eerily similar dreams…

95.text: Why is this the last we’ll see of Mr. Grimm? Also featuring, “The Man Who Stole a Skyscraper”!
